title: For Sale:  Colt Combat Government 45 with "Double Strike" on name
postcontent:
The Combat Government was an attempt by Colt to have a separate model that incorporated some of the features becoming popular with combat-style shooters. Hi profile sights, a lowered & flared ejection port, serrated front strap, beveled mag well, long trigger, flat housing, and wrap-around grips (which of course covered up the front strap serrations. I'm selling my Colt 70 Series Combat Government 45. S/N 70B431xx. This model was made at the end of the 70 series of 1911's as a limited edition of around 1,500 made in 1983. This all original Colt had the name "Combat Government" struck twice at the factory. You can see it in the close-up photo. All the rest of the factory imprinting is crisp. The fiery bluing doesn't show well in most of the photos, but check out the reflection in the slide on the photo of the backstrap. There is a small amount if freckling on the right side of the slide, and there is a 1/2 inch circular mark on the right rear of the slide and frame. This is a tight gun and an excellent shooter as well as being a very rare Colt.

$1,650.00 cash only. Face to face transaction. 
You must be 21 and have a valid FL DL.

I have had a lot of you email me to ask for my phone number. If you include your phone number in your email, then I will call you back.

title: For Sale:  M1 Garand built by Ted Brown - Deal Pending -
postcontent: This is a nice one...I had Ted Brown (one of the top M1/M1A builders) make this rifle for me a few years ago. I wanted a tough as nails rifle but still really accurate. I had him install a Fulton Armory chrome lined barrel. Very few gunsmiths will install a chrome lined barrel on an M1 because it is difficult to headspace. It will last forever and is really easy to clean. He installed a Badger Ordnance NM gas cylinder, and fit the op-rod tip to fit perfectly in the cylinder. The rest of the gun was built using excellent to new GI parts. Shot less than 300 rounds. I initally had the wood painted camo, but have since removed the paint except for inside the stock, as you can't see it without taking it apart, and it keeps the wood sealed. It is not glass bedded, but wood fit is very tight. Has a couple of dings in stock, very minor. I will also include 1 bandoleer of ammo, and a Holbrook device. I have over $2000 in the gun. It will shoot 2 MOA with HXP. I will sell without stock/handguards for $1075, or if you have your own parts and want to rebuild to your liking, I would sell the receiver/bolt/barrel for $700. If you want, you can purchase extra ammo in bandoleers, boxes, in sealed or open cans. Also I have once fired brass and about 500 or so primers. I'll sell the ammo at current CMP pricing, or match any price you can find by a retailer so you will save on shipping.
